{"title": "Harvard Square bookstore mocks Kellyanne Conway\u2019s \u2018Bowling Green massacre\u2019 - The Boston Globe", "url": "https://www.bostonglobe.com/news/politics/2017/02/08/harvard-square-bookstore-mocks-kellyanne-conway-bowling-green-massacre/jKlQZHhash9VBZy4KV1CQO/story.html", "text": "Kellyanne Conway prior to a forum at Harvard University's Kennedy School of Government in Cambridge.\n\nA Harvard Square bookstore is having some fun with Kellyanne Conway\u2019s \u201cBowling Green massacre\u201d gaffe.\n\nThe Harvard Book Store posted a photo on Instagram Wednesday advertising a section dedicated to \u201ccommemorating the victims of the Bowling Green Massacre.\u201d The section was filled with books with titles like \u201cAnit-Intellectualism in American Life,\u201d \u201cThe Anatomy of Fascism,\u201d and \u201cThe Plot Against America.\u201d\n\nAdvertisement\n\nLast week, Conway defended President Donald Trump\u2019s travel ban in an interview with Chris Matthews by citing the \u201cBowling Green Massacre\u201d that prompted former President Obama to impose restrictions on Iraqi refugees.\n\nNo such massacre took place. Conway tweeted Friday morning that she meant to say \u201cBowling Green terrorists\u201d during the interview, referring to the arrest of two men in Kentucky charged with plotting to send weapons and money to Al Qaeda operatives.\n\nIn the time since the interview, Conway has been mocked on social media and a satirical website dedicated to the \u201cvictims\u201d of Bowling Green appeared online, with a donate link that directed users to the ACLU.", "source": "BostonGlobe.com", "publish_date": "2017-02-08", "type": "article"}